NIfTI B&W and DICOM COLOR IMAGES (PoC)

See What is a non-capturing group in regular expressions?.

kind = "image_base|nifti_color|dicom_color"

splitter = glue::glue(
  "^(5_nifti)/([0-9]+)/({kind})(:?/.*/.*)?/.*\\.(?:img|dcm)$"
)
column_names = c("series", "inumber", "kind", "tmp")

NOTE: Debug the regexp with stringr::str_view.

library(purrr)  # %>%, compose

base_images = list.files(
  path = "5_nifti",
  pattern = ".*\\.(img|dcm)$",
  full.names = TRUE,
  recursive = TRUE
) %>%
  stringr::str_subset(kind)

images_info = nifti_info(
    base_images, into = column_names, regex = splitter
  ) %>%
  dplyr::select(
    series, inumber, kind, `xyz`, `pixel resolution [mm]`, file_name
  ) %>%
  dplyr::arrange(inumber, kind)
images_info %>% dplyr::select(-file_name)

Plot DICOM images in color

library(cowplot)
dicom_info <- images_info %>% dplyr::filter(kind == "dicom_color")
dicom_plots = map(dicom_info$file_name, plotColorDICOM)

Check for pure Red and Blue colors in DICOM images
